    "Furthermore, all these techniques are shallow models, which means they cannot fully delve into the intricate relationships between drugs and their respective targets.Nevertheless, these methods predominantly depend on the similarity and interaction data of drug proteins, often overlooking the potential insights from other available data sources.",
